-- Shares in Italy's Anima drop sharply on the day of market debut
-- 
-- Wed Apr 16, 2014 03:14AM EDT
-- None



MILAN, April 16 (Reuters) - Shares in asset manager Anima Holding <ANIM.MI> dropped more than 7 percent on their first day of trading on the Italian stock market.

By 0707 GMT the stock was trading at 3.9 euros a share, down 6 percent. Italy's all-share index <.FTITLMS> rose 1.3 percent.